<topic xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0"><title>normalize-hostnames()</title><indexterm><primary>normalize-hostnames()</primary></indexterm><indexterm><primary>normalize_hostnames()</primary></indexterm><informaltable frame="topbot" colsep="0" rowsep="0"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colnum="1" colwidth="80pt"/><tbody><row><entry>Accepted values:</entry><entry><userinput>yes</userinput> | <userinput>no</userinput> </entry></row><row><entry>Default:</entry><entry><userinput>no</userinput> </entry></row></tbody></tgroup></informaltable><para><emphasis role="bold">Description:</emphasis> If enabled (<userinput>normalize-hostnames(yes)</userinput>), &abbrev; converts the hostnames to lowercase.</para><note><para>This setting applies only to hostnames resolved from DNS. It has no effect if the <parameter>keep-hostname()</parameter> option is enabled, and the message contains a hostname.</para></note></topic>
